# ── Daily Tool: your AI key ────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Bring ANY ONE of these three keys. The app auto-detects which one you set.
# Google is the free, no-card option and the recommended default for the
# workshop. If you set more than one, the order is Anthropic > OpenAI > Google.
#
# Google (free, no credit card):
#   1. Go to https://aistudio.google.com and sign in with a PERSONAL Gmail
#      account (18+). Work/school Google accounts are sometimes blocked.
#   2. Accept the terms, open "API Keys", copy your key.
# Anthropic:  https://console.anthropic.com  (Settings -> API keys)
# OpenAI:     https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
#
# Then duplicate this file as `.env` and paste your key into the matching line
# below (leave the others blank). Your key stays on the server side of the app
# and is never sent to the browser. To switch later, change the key and restart
# the app; clear it to fall back to the shared key if one is configured.
#
# Heads up: free-tier prompts may be used by the provider to improve its
# products. Don't paste anything personal or confidential.

GOOGLE_API_KEY=paste-your-key-here
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Optional: pin a specific model. Defaults per provider:
#   google/gemini-2.5-flash  ·  anthropic/claude-3.5-haiku  ·  openai/gpt-4.1-mini
# MODEL=google/gemini-2.5-flash

# CopilotKit sends anonymous usage telemetry by default. Uncomment to opt out.
# COPILOTKIT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=true

# ── Shared key via Cloudflare AI Gateway (optional; the host sets this) ──
#
# If the workshop host provides a funded gateway, these are set FOR you in the
# Codespace and you do not paste any key above: leave the key lines blank and
# you run on the shared, spend-capped gateway. Paste your own key above to use
# it instead (your key always wins); clear it to return to the gateway.
# Do NOT also set MODEL here; use CF_AIG_MODEL to pick the gateway's model.
# CF_AIG_ACCOUNT_ID=
# CF_AIG_GATEWAY_ID=
# CF_AIG_TOKEN=
# CF_AIG_MODEL=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5
# CF_AIG_PROVIDER_KEY=   # only for BYOK pass-through; unset for Unified Billing

# ── Deploying live to Cloudflare? ──────────────────────────────────────
#
# This .env file is for running the app on your own machine. To put the app
# live on the web, you do NOT use this file. The Deploy-to-Cloudflare button
# (see the README) asks you for your key in the browser and stores it as an
# encrypted Cloudflare Secret on your own Worker. The secret field names live
# in `.dev.vars.example`.
